  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening HIV testing and counselling services</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose of this project is to strengthen the provision of HIV testing and counselling (HTC) services to at-risk groups in urban and rural Lilongwe. 
Operating within the Malawi Extended National Framework coordinated by the National AIDS Commission, CAFOD&#x2019;s partner The Lighthouse Trust will focus on: 
- the provision of HTC to TB suspects and patients at Martin Preuss Centre, STI patients at Bwaila Hospital and inmates at Maula Central Prison;
- increasing HTC uptake among pregnant and lactating women, at 25 rural health centres;
- continued routine counselling and testing of the general population in all its sites, and development of linkages with the community home based care (CHBC) programs; 
- tracing and follow-up of infected infants, so as to enhance their linkage to antiretroviral treatment (ART) and related services; 
- psychosocial support for adolescents;
- ongoing support, with the Ministry of Health, to all major counselling and testing sites nationwide.</narrative>
  </description>
